EDUPAY SCHOOL — OFFICIAL HANDBOOK & FEE POLICY DOCUMENT
========================================================

CHAPTER 1: FEE STRUCTURE
--------------------------

1.1 Tuition Fees
The annual tuition fee varies by class level:
- Classes 1-5 (Primary): ₹25,000 per annum
- Classes 6-8 (Middle School): ₹35,000 per annum
- Classes 9-10 (Secondary): ₹45,000 per annum
- Classes 11-12 (Senior Secondary): ₹55,000 per annum

Tuition fees can be paid in quarterly installments:
- Q1 (April-June): Due by April 15
- Q2 (July-September): Due by July 15
- Q3 (October-December): Due by October 15
- Q4 (January-March): Due by January 15

1.2 Examination Fees
- Term Examination Fee: ₹2,000 per term (2 terms per year)
- Board Examination Fee (Class 10 & 12): ₹5,000 (one-time, due by December 31)

1.3 Library Fee
- Annual Library Fee: ₹1,500 (due at the start of the academic year)
- Lost/Damaged Book Fee: Actual cost of the book + ₹200 processing fee

1.4 Laboratory Fee (Classes 6-12)
- Science Lab Fee: ₹3,000 per annum
- Computer Lab Fee: ₹2,500 per annum

1.5 Sports & Activity Fee
- Annual Sports Fee: ₹2,000
- Extra-curricular Activity Fee: ₹1,500

CHAPTER 2: LATE FEE POLICY
----------------------------

2.1 Grace Period
A grace period of 15 days is provided after each due date. No late fee is charged during this period.

2.2 Late Fee Charges
After the grace period:
- Days 16-30 past due: ₹50 per day late fee
- Days 31-60 past due: ₹100 per day late fee
- Beyond 60 days: ₹100 per day + written notice to parents

2.3 Late Fee Waiver
Late fees may be waived in the following circumstances:
- Medical emergency (with valid medical certificate)
- Natural disaster affecting the family
- Death in the immediate family
- Other extraordinary circumstances approved by the Principal

Applications for late fee waiver must be submitted within 7 days of the payment with supporting documents.

CHAPTER 3: REFUND POLICY
--------------------------

3.1 Full Refund
A full refund of tuition fees (minus registration fee) is available if:
- Withdrawal request is submitted within 15 days of admission
- The student has not attended more than 5 classes

3.2 Partial Refund
- Withdrawal within 30 days of term start: 75% refund
- Withdrawal within 60 days of term start: 50% refund
- Withdrawal after 60 days: No refund

3.3 Non-Refundable Fees
The following fees are non-refundable under any circumstances:
- Registration/Admission fee
- Examination fees (if exams have been conducted)
- Library fee (if books have been issued)

CHAPTER 4: SCHOLARSHIP & FINANCIAL AID
-----------------------------------------

4.1 Merit Scholarship
- Top 3 students in each class receive:
  - 1st Rank: 50% tuition fee waiver
  - 2nd Rank: 30% tuition fee waiver
  - 3rd Rank: 15% tuition fee waiver

4.2 Need-Based Financial Aid
- Families with annual income below ₹3,00,000 may apply for financial aid
- Financial aid covers up to 75% of tuition fees
- Application deadline: March 31 of each year
- Required documents: Income certificate, Aadhaar card, Bank statement

4.3 Sibling Discount
- 2nd child enrolled: 10% discount on tuition
- 3rd child enrolled: 20% discount on tuition

CHAPTER 5: PAYMENT METHODS
-----------------------------

5.1 Accepted Payment Methods
- Online Payment via EduPay App (recommended — instant confirmation)
- Bank Transfer/NEFT (Account details available in the app)
- UPI Payment (School UPI ID available in the app)
- Cash payment at school office (receipt will be issued)
- Cheque payment (payable to "EduPay School Trust")

5.2 Early Payment Benefits
- 5% discount on annual fees if paid in full before April 30
- 2% discount on quarterly fees if paid 15 days before due date

5.3 EMI Option
- For fees above ₹20,000, EMI option is available through partner banks
- EMI duration: 3, 6, or 12 months
- Interest rate: 0% for 3-month EMI, 6% p.a. for longer durations

CHAPTER 6: COMMUNICATION POLICY
---------------------------------

6.1 Fee-Related Communications
- Monthly fee status updates via EduPay App notifications
- Email reminders 7 days before due date
- SMS alerts on the due date
- Physical notice after 30 days of non-payment

6.2 Dispute Resolution
- Fee disputes must be raised within 30 days of the charge
- Contact: fees@edupayschool.com or visit the accounts office
- Resolution timeline: 7-10 working days

6.3 Parent-Teacher Communication
- AI Assistant available 24/7 in the EduPay App for policy queries
- School office hours: Monday-Friday, 9:00 AM - 4:00 PM
- Email response time: Within 24 hours on working days

